                            <comment id="12591828" author="stack" created="Wed, 23 Apr 2008 22:24:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking this as a 0.2.0 because its easy and API is changing a load in 0.2.0 so lets get it all in in the one go.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12591844" author="jimk" created="Wed, 23 Apr 2008 22:41:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-82&quot; title=&quot;row keys should be array of bytes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-82&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-82&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; will be changing row keys to byte[] overloading doesn&apos;t make sense.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12591862" author="bryanduxbury" created="Wed, 23 Apr 2008 23:13:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jim, this isn&apos;t about keys. This is about uses in things like the HTable constructor, where byte[] will NOT replace Text. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12591865" author="jimk" created="Wed, 23 Apr 2008 23:19:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, my misunderstanding. I thought it was about overloading methods that take row keys.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
